---
import Page from '../../layouts/Page.astro';
import SectionBanner from '../../components/ui/SectionBanner.astro';
---

<Page
  title="AI-Enhanced Services"
  description="AI tools integrated into real production workflows. Batch processing, render correction, ComfyUI pipelines, rapid concept variations. Vision Graphics Kft."
>

  <SectionBanner
    image="/_img/banners/banner-ai.jpg"
    label="Useful AI. Not Hype."
    title="AI-Enhanced Services"
    size="page"
    headingLevel="h1"
  />
  <div class="service-page">

    <div class="service-breadcrumb">
      <a href="/services/">Services</a>
      <span>→</span>
      <span>AI-Enhanced Services</span>
    </div>

    <p class="section-label">Service</p>
    <h2 class="display-lg service-h1">AI-Enhanced Services</h2>
    <p class="service-tagline-large">Useful AI. Not hype.</p>

    <div class="service-body-grid">
      <div class="service-main">

        <p class="service-lead">
          Let's skip the AI buzzwords. We'll show you which tools work best, help you
          dodge common mistakes, and tell you where AI doesn't help. Not every problem
          needs an AI solution — we'll tell you which parts of your project will benefit
          and which won't.
        </p>

        <h2 class="service-section-h2">What we actually do with AI</h2>
        <div class="deliverable-grid">
          {[
            {
              title: 'Rapid Concept Variations',
              desc: 'ComfyUI / SwarmUI pipelines generate material, lighting, and design variations quickly — so you can explore options without full re-renders for each.',
            },
            {
              title: 'Batch Image Processing',
              desc: 'Automated pipelines for processing large render batches: colour correction, format conversion, watermarking, and quality checks at scale.',
            },
            {
              title: 'AI-Assisted Render Correction',
              desc: 'Upscaling, noise reduction, and detail enhancement on existing renders. Useful for repurposing older project imagery.',
            },
            {
              title: 'Automated File Organisation',
              desc: 'Custom scripts and AI-assisted tools for organizing, naming, and cataloguing large visual archives.',
            },
            {
              title: 'Inpainting & Compositing',
              desc: 'Precise AI-assisted inpainting for removing unwanted elements, filling in details, or extending compositions.',
            },
            {
              title: 'Style Exploration',
              desc: 'AI-generated mood references to explore visual direction before committing to full 3D production.',
            },
          ].map(d => (
            <div class="deliverable-card">
              <h3 class="deliverable-title">{d.title}</h3>
              <p class="deliverable-desc">{d.desc}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>

      </div>

      <aside class="service-sidebar">
        <div class="sidebar-block">
          <h3 class="sidebar-label">Tools we use</h3>
          <ul class="sidebar-list">
            <li>ComfyUI / SwarmUI</li>
            <li>Stable Diffusion + ControlNet</li>
            <li>Topaz AI</li>
            <li>Python automation</li>
            <li>Custom MAXScript pipelines</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="sidebar-block">
          <h3 class="sidebar-label">Pricing</h3>
          <p class="sidebar-price">By scope</p>
          <p class="sidebar-note">AI-enhanced work is typically priced as an add-on to a standard project, or as a standalone batch job. Quote on request.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="sidebar-cta">
          <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-primary sidebar-btn">Get a Quote</a>
          <a href="/vision-tech/" class="btn btn-ghost">Our tech stack</a>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>

  </div>

  <SectionBanner
    image="/_img/banners/banner-general.jpg"
    label="Creating Images"
    title="Generate. Refine. Done."
    headingLevel="h2"
  />
  <div class="service-section container">
    <p class="section-body">
      Need images? Our AI makes them from scratch — not just architecture. Product shots, concept
      art, marketing materials. Just describe what you want and you'll get options quickly.
      Want to change something? "Make it sunset" or "add some trees" is all it takes.
    </p>
    <ul class="results-list">
      <li>Any image type: architecture, products, concepts, marketing materials</li>
      <li>Natural language control — no special prompt engineering required</li>
      <li>Turn blurry photos into sharp ones</li>
      <li>Fix old or damaged images</li>
      <li>Make sketches look photo-real</li>
      <li>Sort and find images automatically by what's in them</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <SectionBanner
    image="/_img/banners/banner-tech.jpg"
    label="3D & Automation"
    title="Less Manual Work"
    headingLevel="h2"
  />
  <div class="service-section container">
    <p class="section-body">
      Gone are the days of spending weeks on 3D models for early exploration. Tell the AI what
      you want, and it builds it. Got lots of 3D models? Our AI goes through them all and sorts
      them by what's in them — no more digging through old project files.
    </p>
    <ul class="results-list">
      <li>Turn photos into 3D models in hours, not days</li>
      <li>Clean up messy files automatically</li>
      <li>Fix textures that look wrong</li>
      <li>Find and organize models by content</li>
      <li>Automate batch processing of hundreds of renders</li>
      <li>Connect tools together so they actually talk to each other</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <SectionBanner
    image="/_img/banners/banner-workflow.jpg"
    label="Our Position"
    title="AI Where It Actually Helps"
    headingLevel="h2"
  />
  <div class="service-section container">
    <p class="section-body">
      AI tools genuinely accelerate some parts of visualization work — concept exploration,
      batch processing, and certain types of image correction. They don't replace 30 years
      of 3D expertise, scene-building knowledge, or understanding of what makes a render
      actually communicate something.
    </p>
    <p class="section-body">
      We integrate AI where it reduces time and cost without compromising quality.
      These aren't demo tools — they work on real projects. You don't need to be an AI
      expert to use them. And when you need a human to check things, we're here.
    </p>
  </div>

</Page>

<style>
  .service-page {
    max-width: 1060px;
    padding-top: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem);
  }

  .service-breadcrumb {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem;
    font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: var(--fs-xs);
    color: var(--color-text-faint); margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .service-breadcrumb a { color: var(--color-text-muted); text-decoration: none; transition: color 200ms; }
  .service-breadcrumb a:hover { color: var(--color-accent); }

  .service-h1 { margin: 0.5rem 0 0.75rem; }
  .service-tagline-large { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: var(--fs-h6); font-style: italic; color: var(--color-accent); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .service-lead { font-size: var(--fs-small); color: var(--color-text-muted); max-width: 65ch; line-height: 1.75; margin: 0 0 1.5rem; }

  .service-body-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 240px; gap: 4rem; align-items: start; }
  .service-main { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; }

  .service-section-h2 { font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: var(--fs-xs); font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--color-text-faint); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }

  .deliverable-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1px; background: var(--color-border); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .deliverable-card { background: var(--color-surface); padding: 1.5rem; transition: background 200ms; }
  .deliverable-card:hover { background: var(--color-surface-2); }
  .deliverable-title { font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: var(--fs-small); font-weight: 500; color: var(--color-text); margin-bottom: 0.4rem; }
  .deliverable-desc { font-size: var(--fs-xs); color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0; max-width: none; }

  /* Sub-sections */
  .service-section { padding-block: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem); }

  .section-body { font-size: var(--fs-small); color: var(--color-text-muted); max-width: 65ch; line-height: 1.75; margin: 0 0 1.5rem; }
  .section-body:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  .results-list { list-style: none; padding: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.6rem; }
  .results-list li { font-size: var(--fs-small); color: var(--color-text-muted); padding-left: 1.25rem; position: relative; line-height: 1.5; }
  .results-list li::before { content: '→'; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--color-accent); font-size: var(--fs-xs); }

  /* Sidebar */
  .service-sidebar { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 2rem; position: sticky; top: 5rem; }
  .sidebar-block { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.6rem; }
  .sidebar-label { font-family: var(--font-body); font-size: var(--fs-xs); font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--color-text-faint); }
  .sidebar-list { list-style: none; padding: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.35rem; }
  .sidebar-list li { font-size: var(--fs-xs); color: var(--color-text-muted); padding-left: 0.9rem; position: relative; }
  .sidebar-list li::before { content: '—'; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--color-border); font-size: var(--fs-xs); }
  .sidebar-price { font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: var(--fs-h5); font-weight: 300; color: var(--color-text); margin: 0; }
  .sidebar-note { font-size: var(--fs-xs); color: var(--color-text-faint); line-height: 1.5; margin: 0; max-width: none; }
  .sidebar-cta { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; }
  .sidebar-btn { width: 100%; justify-content: center; }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .service-body-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .service-sidebar { position: static; }
    .deliverable-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
